Southern Samity FC

Southern Samity FC, based in Kolkata, is an elite-level Indian professional football team. In the 2010-11 season, the club made their I-League 2nd Division debut. The club finished second in the I-League 2nd Division, 2017-18. In 2020-21, club was a standout performer in the IFA Shield.

LEGACY OF 8 DECADES

Years of hard effort and dedication are defined by the heights of legacy. Keeping the tradition alive, as well as maintaining the framework, are goals that must be met. Success occurred in a variety of forms, each resulting in a new manner to grow together and be proud of one another.The word "legacy" conjures up images of honesty, faith, and community service. Moments are fleeting, but they should be shared for a lifetime.

ABOUT

For the first time in 1945, Southern Samity FC made an enormous mark in Kolkata. Southern Samity was the runner-up in the 2016 I-League 2nd Division, much to the delight of the fans. The club has a clear mission and goals that it hopes to achieve shortly.
